external_knowledge:
The D statistic is a measure used in population genetics to quantify the amount of introgression or gene flow between different species or populations; 
D statistic values range from -1 to 1, where positive values indicate an excess of introgressed sites, and negative values indicate a deficit; 
A high D statistic value indicates a higher degree of introgression or gene flow.

